==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stormy
<hw>Storm"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Stormier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Stormiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Characterized by, or
proceeding from, a storm; subject to storms; agitated with furious
winds; boisterous; tempestuous; <as>as, a <ex>stormy</ex> season; a
<ex>stormy</ex> day or week.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧Beyond the
<xex>stormy</xex> Hebrides.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Proceeding from violent agitation or fury; <as>as, a
<ex>stormy</ex> sound; <ex>stormy</ex> shocks.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Violent; passionate; rough; <as>as, <ex>stormy</ex>
passions</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Stormy</qex> chiefs of a desert but extensive domain.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Storthing</ent>⟦br⟧
